snippet.textDisplay: I saw Jack in his hometown of Athlone in Ireland in August 2014, I literally brushed passed him on a skinny bridge, I stared up at him and he looked back at me, but I was too pussy to say hello to him. I was only 12, and I said to my dad "Dad that's jacksepticeye!" and we both looked back at the back of his head walking away and dad sai "That looks like him, yeah. Do you wanna say hello to him". And I was so nervous and shaky that I was like "No, what if it's not him!" And dad just said "Alright, fair enough" or something. I regretted not speaking to him for like a year, and it's now almost 2020 and the memories of that day are flooding back again and I'm getting proper emotional over the fact that I could have spoken to Jacksepticeye, but chose not to. Especially since back then he only had 1 million subs, and now he has 23 million subs, several TV appearances and is interviewing celebrities such as Dwayne Johnson and Jack Black. And Arnold Schwarzenegger! So this is a message for everyone reading, if fate hands you an opportunity that you may never get again, seize it while you can! Otherwise you might end up regretting it for years and years. Thanks so much for reading. I had to get my story out there.
